#- Worship of the Ancient Ones in History
"Let them curse it that curse the day, who are skilful to rouse Leviathan." - JOB 3:9

S.H. Hooke, in his excellent Middle Eastern Mythology, tells us that the Leviathan 
mentioned in JOB, and  elsewhere in the Old
#- Testament, is the Hebrew name given to the 
Serpent TIAMAT, and reveals that there was in existence either a cult, or scattered 
individuals, who worshipped or called up the Serpent of the Sea, or Abyss. Indeed, the Hebrew word for Abyss that is found in 
#- GENESIS 1:2, Hooke tells us, tehom, which the majority of scholars take to be a survival of the name of the chaos-dragon TIAMAT of Leviathan that is identified closely with Cthulhu within the pages are mentioned independently of each other, indicating 

#- that somehow Cthulhu is the male counterpart of TIAMAT.  
   This monster is well known to cult worship all over the world. In China, however, there is an interesting twist. Far from being considered a completely hostile creature, dedicated to the erasure
#- of mankind from the page of existence, the Dragon is given a place of pre-eminence and one does not hear of a Chinese angel or saint striving to slay the dragon but rather to cultivate it. The Chinese system of geomancy, feng shui (pronounced Fung Shway) 
#- is the science of understanding the "dragon currents" which exist beneath  the earth, these same telluric energies that are distilled in such places as Chartes Cathedral in France, Glastonbury in the England, and the Ziggurats of Mesopotamia. In both
#- European and Chinese cultures, the Dragon or serpent is said to reside somewhere "below the earth"; it is a powerful force, a magickal force, which is identified with mystery over the created world; it is also a power that can be summoned by the few and 
#- not the many.

Nor is it to be thought that man is either the oldest or the last of Earth's masters, or that the common bulk of life and substance walks alone. The Old Ones were, the Old Ones are, and the Old Ones shall be. Not in the spaces we know but 
#- between them, they walk serene and primal, undimensioned and to us unseen. Yog-Sothoth knowns the gate. Yog-Sothoth is the gate. Yog-Sothoth is the key and guardian of the gate. Past, present, future, all are one in Yog-Sothoth. He knows where the 
#- Old Ones broke through of old, and where they shall break through again. He knows where they have trod Earth's field, and where they still tread them, and why no one can behold them as the tread. Their hand is at your throats, yet we see them not; and 
#- their habitation is even one with your guarded threshold. Yog-Sothoth is the key to the gate. Man rules now where They once ruled; They shall soon rule where man rules now. After summer is winter, after winter is summer. They wait patient and potent, for 
#- here shall They reign again.  


The Godess of The Witches

   The current revival of the cult called Wicca is a manifestation of the ancient secret societies that sought to tap this occult force and use it to
#- their own advantage, and to the advantage of humanity as was the original intent.  The Goddess has also been worshipped all over the world, under many names, but is still essentially the same Goddess.

The Horned Moon
   The God of The Moon, NANNA in 
#- Sumerian mythology, later called SIN. In both cases he was the Father of the Gods(of the planetary realm) depicted as wearing horns, a symbol familiar to the witches as a representative of their God. The horn shaped crown is illustrative of the cresent 

#- phases of the Moon and were symbolic of divinity in many cultures around the world. In Sumeria and Egypt horns were solely representative of evil gods. The attempts by the Christian Church to eradicate pagan faiths horns are a symbol of Satan, the Author 
#- of Evil. Satan, which depicted as half-animal, half-human creature with horns, claws, and sometimes a tail. The church's use of horns as the archetype of Evil is quite similar to the feeling many people have today with the swastika used by the Nazis, a 
#- symbol which has become an archetype of evil in the west. Side by side with the worship of Nanna there was the fear of a the demon, PAZUZU, the Beast.

The Devil
  Panzuzu was the prime example of the type of Devil the sumerians were
#- particularly aware of, which was constantly depicted in their carvings and statues. The purpose of these carvings were to ward off the spiritual and psychic which would precipitate a plague. "Evil to Destroy Evil"
While Christianity states that Lucifer 
#- was a rebel in heavenand fell from God's grace, the originial story is that of MURDUK was the rebel, and severed the body of the Ancient of Ancient Ones to create the cosmos. 
