THE CONJURATION OF THE WATCHER
☆ ≸ ⋏
These symbols must be engraved upon the bowl with a fine stylus, or painted with dark 
#- ink. The sacrifice must be new bread, pine resin, and the glass Olieribos. These must be burned in a new bowl. The Watcher will depart when he is given license to depart.

The Watcher comes from a race different from that of Men and yet difference from 
#- that of the Gods, and it is said that he was with Kingu and his hordes at the time of the War between the Worlds. Wherefore it is wise to conjure it in the Names of the Three Great Watchers. Who existed before the confrontation from whose born the Watcher
#- and his race ultimately derive and those Three are Anu, Enlil, and Master Enki of the Magick Waters. And this is the reason they are sometimes called the Three Watchers. The Watcher appears sometimes as a great and fierce dog who prowls the Gate or the 

#- Circle, frightening away the idimmu who forever lurk about the barriers waiting for sacrifice. While other times the Watcher appears as the Enemy, ready to devour the priest who has blundered in the incantations or neglected the sacrifice. 
